Second state record, pending review and acceptance.  Originally located by call note overhead, but not to species level.  Bird landed on beach within a few hundred meters, took flight and circled us a few times, and moved on south after not more than 5 min.  Army of great Massachusetts birders present at discovery--Iliff, both Trimbles, Davies, Seitz, Johnson, Faherety, Garvey, and so on.  Many photos were taken at the time, as can be heard in the background of the recording.  Appears to be an adult female.    Recording not modified other than trimming out playback from other folks, and trimmed fainter and weaker calls.  Bird did not give full "keeowee" call but once or twice overhead.
